div1.p: Order Discharging Writ and Withdrawing Exhibits
In the Matter of the Application of Moy Hing Hun for a Writ of Habeas Corpus

In this matter, petition for a writ of habeas corpus having heretofore been filed and order having been granted requiring Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration, to show cause why a writ of habeas corpus should not be issued herein, and the writ having been issued on the day of October, 1921, and the court having considered the evidence and having heard the argument of counsel thereon; it is hereby

ORDERED, ADJUDGED and DECREED that the said writ of habeas corpus be, and it is hereby, discharged, and that the petitioner remain in the custody of the said Henry M. White Commissioner of Immigration; and it is hereby further
ORDERED that the exhibits attached to the return of Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration, filed herein, be withdrawn, to be delivered to the said Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration.
DONE in open court this 17th day of November, 1921.
In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington
In Re Appln of Moy Hing Hung for Writ of Habeas Corpus
Order Dischrging Writ and Withdrawing Exhibits
Filed in the United States District Court
